project tradesdb {
  database_type: 'postgresql'
  note: '''
  # Algorithmic Trading Database (`tradesdb`)

  Operational store for a **broker-agnostic algorithmic trading system**, hosted on
  **PostgreSQL v17.10** on the same cluster as `macrodb` and `stocksdb`. Owns the
  *trading-private* state of the platform — strategies, capital allocation, risk
  rules, generated signals, the order/execution lifecycle, position & P&L facts,
  circuit-breaker events, and an immutable audit trail.

  Designed to back the `growthio/algotraders` Python library and to support the full
  automation spectrum: signal-only (A) → human-approved (B) → fully automated (C),
  with a parallel paper-trading mode that shares the same code path as live.

  **Reference master data is never owned here** — securities, exchanges, symbol
  mappings, derivative contracts and currencies are *subscribed* read-only from
  `macrodb` / `stocksdb` (see Logical Replication below). Trading facts reference
  that data through ordinary foreign keys into the local subscription tables, while
  the subscription tables themselves carry **no incoming foreign keys** (dropped on
  the subscriber side to avoid apply-order failures).

  ## Schema Layout

  | schema    | purpose                                                                    |
  |:----------|:---------------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `public`  | Bootstrap reference data — broker integrations master.                     |
  | `common`  | Trading masters (account, strategy, risk) + macrodb/stocksdb subscriptions.|
  | `private` | Transactional facts (signals, orders, fills, positions, P&L) + audit log.  |
  | `dev`     | Developer/auditor user-defined functions only — *no tables*.               |

  ## Table Naming Convention

  - `*_mw` → **M**aster, **W**orld scope (slowly-changing reference / config data).
  - `*_tx` → **T**ransactional fact table (append-mostly rows).

  ## Logical Replication (Subscriptions)

  All reference tables in `common` are read-only and populated via PostgreSQL
  logical replication subscriptions. `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` are revoked from
  `PUBLIC` on every subscribed table, and all incoming foreign-key constraints are
  omitted on the subscriber side. Each subscribed table keeps its primary key so it
  can serve as the replica identity required for `UPDATE` / `DELETE` apply.

  | Subscription                    | Source DB  | Source Publication            | Tables                                                          |
  |:--------------------------------|:-----------|:------------------------------|:----------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `macrodb_currency_reference`    | `macrodb`  | `macrodb_currency_table`      | `common.currency_mw`                                            |
  | `stocksdb_securities_reference` | `stocksdb` | `stocksdb_securities_table`   | `common.securities_mw`, `common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`  |
  | `stocksdb_exchange_reference`   | `stocksdb` | `stocksdb_exchange_table`     | `common.stock_exchange_mw`                                      |
  | `stocksdb_derivative_reference` | `stocksdb` | `stocksdb_derivative_table`   | `common.derivative_contract_mw`                                 |

  > **Cross-repo dependency:** the three `stocksdb_*` publications above must be
  > created on `stocksdb` (it currently publishes nothing). `macrodb_currency_table`
  > already exists. See [publication.conf.sql](database/publication.conf.sql).

  ## Custom Enum Types (PostgreSQL — Not Representable in DBML Free Tier)

  | Type                          | Values                                                                                              | Used in                                   |
  |:------------------------------|:----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|:------------------------------------------|
  | `common.timeframe_value`      | `1m, 3m, 5m, 15m, 1h, 1D, 1M, 1Y` (8)                                                                | `common.strategy_mw.timeframe`            |
  | `common.strategy_stage`       | `A, B, C, RETIRED` (4)                                                                               | `common.strategy_mw.strategy_stage`       |
  | `common.signal_source`        | `STRATEGY, TRADINGVIEW, MANUAL` (3)                                                                  | `*.signal_source`                         |
  | `common.allocation_policy`    | `STATIC_PCT, DYNAMIC_FREEFLOAT` (2)                                                                  | `common.strategy_allocation_mw`           |
  | `common.risk_scope`           | `ACCOUNT, STRATEGY, PORTFOLIO` (3)                                                                   | `common.risk_rule_mw`, circuit events     |
  | `common.risk_rule_type`       | `PER_TRADE_SL, POSITION_SIZE, DAILY_MAX_LOSS, MAX_POSITIONS, SINGLE_ISIN_EXPOSURE, SECTOR_CONC` (6)  | `common.risk_rule_mw.risk_rule_type`      |
  | `private.instrument_kind`     | `EQUITY, DERIVATIVE` (2)                                                                             | signals / orders / positions / universe   |
  | `private.signal_action`       | `BUY, SELL, EXIT_LONG, EXIT_SHORT` (4)                                                               | `private.signal_tx.signal_action`         |
  | `private.signal_status`       | `PENDING, VALIDATED, APPROVED, REJECTED, EXPIRED` (5)                                                | `private.signal_tx.signal_status`         |
  | `private.order_side`          | `BUY, SELL` (2)                                                                                      | `private.order_tx.order_side`             |
  | `private.order_type`          | `MARKET, LIMIT, SL, SL_M` (4)                                                                        | `private.order_tx.order_type`             |
  | `private.order_variety`       | `REGULAR, BRACKET, COVER, AMO` (4)                                                                   | `private.order_tx.order_variety`          |
  | `private.product_type`        | `CNC, INTRADAY, MARGIN, NORMAL` (4)                                                                  | `private.order_tx.product_type`           |
  | `private.order_status`        | `PENDING_APPROVAL, APPROVED, REJECTED, SUBMITTED, OPEN, PARTIALLY_FILLED, FILLED, CANCELLED, EXPIRED, FAILED` (10) | `private.order_tx.order_status` |
  | `private.approval_source`     | `DASHBOARD, TELEGRAM, AUTO` (3)                                                                      | `private.order_tx.approval_source`        |
  | `private.execution_mode`      | `LIVE, PAPER, BACKTEST` (3)                                                                          | every `_tx` table                         |
  | `private.actor_type`          | `SYSTEM, STRATEGY, USER, BROKER` (4)                                                                 | `private.audit_log_tx.actor_type`         |

  Enum columns are represented as `varchar` in this diagram.

  ## Execution Modes

  Every transactional fact carries `execution_mode` (`LIVE` / `PAPER` / `BACKTEST`).
  The same strategy class runs in all three modes against the same tables; promotion
  through stages A → B → C is governed purely by `common.strategy_mw.strategy_stage`,
  never by a code fork.

  ## CI/CD

  Managed through **Project Archon**, mirroring the migration & deploy pattern used
  by `macrodb` and `stocksdb`. Schema migrations run via Alembic ahead of each
  rolling restart on the host.
  '''
}


// ============================================================================
// public schema — operational bootstrap
// ============================================================================

table public.broker_mw {
  broker_code            char(5)      [pk] // pk_broker_code
  broker_name            varchar(64)  [not null, unique] // uq_broker_name
  broker_desc            varchar(256) [not null]
  broker_uri             varchar(128) [not null, unique] // uq_broker_uri
  supports_websocket     boolean      [not null, default: false]
  supports_bracket_order boolean      [not null, default: false]
  is_active              boolean      [not null, default: true]

  note: '''
  ## Broker Master (`mw` = Master-World)

  Master list of broker integrations the platform can authenticate and trade
  through. Acts as the dimensional lookup behind every order placed and every
  account opened. Capability flags (`supports_websocket`, `supports_bracket_order`)
  let the order manager and ticker service degrade gracefully per broker.

  > **Note:** `broker_uri` must store a bare base URL only — never a query string,
  > token, or embedded credential. Live secrets (API keys, TOTP seeds) are held in
  > the host secret store, **never** in this database.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_account_broker_code`
  - **`private.order_tx`** — `fk_order_broker_code`

  ### Seeded Values

  `FYERS` (Fyers API v3), `ZRDHA` (Zerodha Kite — future), `PAPER` (in-house paper
  trading simulator) — see `database/schema/public/seed/broker.sql`.
  '''
}


// ============================================================================
// common schema — subscribed reference data (read-only · bare · no incoming FKs)
// ============================================================================

table common.currency_mw {
  currency_code     char(3)     [pk] // pk_currency_code
  currency_name     varchar(64) [not null, unique] // uq_currency_name
  currency_symbol   varchar(16) [unique] // uq_currency_symbol
  currency_type     char(1)     [not null]
  currency_subtype  char(1)
  n_decimals        integer     [not null, default: 2]
  minor_unit_name   varchar(32)
  minor_unit_symbol varchar(16)
  minor_unit_factor integer

  note: '''
  ## Currency Reference (`_mw`) — MacroDB Subscription

  Read-only ISO 4217 currency reference. Populated via logical replication
  subscription `macrodb_currency_reference` from publication `macrodb_currency_table`
  on the MacroDB reference database. `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` are revoked from
  `PUBLIC`. All incoming foreign-key constraints are omitted on the subscriber side.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_account_base_currency` (account denomination)
  '''
}

table common.securities_mw {
  security_isin_code   char(12)     [pk] // pk_security_isin_code
  security_description varchar(255) [not null]
  security_issuer_name varchar(255)
  security_issuer_type varchar(64) // enum: stocksdb common.security_issue_type
  isin_data_source_id  char(5)      [not null]

  indexes {
    security_issuer_type [name: 'ix_securities_mw_security_issuer_type']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Securities Reference (`_mw`) — StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only ISIN-keyed securities master. Populated via logical replication
  subscription `stocksdb_securities_reference` from publication
  `stocksdb_securities_table` on the StocksDB operational database. `INSERT /
  UPDATE / DELETE` are revoked from `PUBLIC`; incoming foreign keys are omitted.

  Mirrors the source column shape exactly. `isin_data_source_id` is retained as a
  plain column (the `public.data_source_mw` it points to lives in StocksDB and is
  *not* subscribed here).

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** — logical reference (no FK — both are subscription tables)
  - **`private.position_snapshot_tx`** / tax lots — by ISIN (delivery aggregation)
  '''
}

table common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw {
  ses_primary_id         integer      [pk] // pk_securities_exchange_symbol_id (replicated value — not locally generated)
  security_isin_code     char(12)     [not null]
  market_identifier_code char(4)      [not null]
  exchange_symbol        varchar(32)  [not null]
  exchange_symbol_name   varchar(255) [not null]
  symbol_series_code     varchar(16)
  ses_data_source_id     char(5)      [not null]
  created_on             timestamptz  [not null]

  indexes {
    market_identifier_code [name: 'ix_ses_mw_market_identifier_code']
    symbol_series_code     [name: 'ix_ses_mw_symbol_series_code']
    exchange_symbol        [name: 'ix_ses_mw_exchange_symbol']
    (security_isin_code, market_identifier_code, exchange_symbol, exchange_symbol_name) [unique, name: 'uq_exchange_symbol']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Securities Exchange Symbol Reference (`_mw`) — StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only ISIN → exchange-symbol bridge. Populated via subscription
  `stocksdb_securities_reference` from publication `stocksdb_securities_table`.
  `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` are revoked from `PUBLIC`; incoming foreign keys are
  omitted.

  > **Note:** `ses_primary_id` is the equity trading grain of the whole platform —
  > it is the value persisted on signals, orders, positions and the StocksDB price
  > time-series. Locally it is a plain `integer` primary key (the identity sequence
  > lives on the publisher); it is **not** `generated ... as identity` here.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.strategy_universe_mw`** — `fk_universe_ses_primary_id` (equity leg)
  - **`private.signal_tx`** — `fk_signal_ses_primary_id`
  - **`private.order_tx`** — `fk_order_ses_primary_id`
  - **`private.position_snapshot_tx`** — `fk_position_ses_primary_id`
  '''
}

table common.stock_exchange_mw {
  market_identifier_code    char(4)     [pk] // pk_market_identifier_code
  operating_mic_code        char(4)     [not null]
  legal_exchange_name       varchar(64) [not null]
  scock_exchange_acronym    varchar(16) // preserved typo — matches live StocksDB schema
  stock_exchange_country_id char(3)     [not null]
  registered_city_code      char(5)
  trading_currency_code     char(3)     [not null]
  operational_from          date        [not null]
  operational_to            date
  data_source_id            char(5)     [not null]

  indexes {
    (stock_exchange_country_id, legal_exchange_name) [unique, name: 'uq_stock_exchange_name']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Stock Exchange Reference (`_mw`) — StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only ISO 10383 MIC-coded exchange master. Populated via subscription
  `stocksdb_exchange_reference` from publication `stocksdb_exchange_table`. `INSERT /
  UPDATE / DELETE` are revoked from `PUBLIC`; incoming foreign keys are omitted.

  `stock_exchange_country_id`, `registered_city_code` and `trading_currency_code`
  are retained as plain columns (their parents — country / city / currency — are not
  all subscribed into `tradesdb`, and subscriber-side FKs are dropped regardless).
  The `scock_exchange_acronym` typo is preserved to match the live source schema.

  ### Referenced By

  - Resolved through `ses_primary_id` / `derivative_contract_id`; no direct FK from trading facts.
  '''
}

table common.derivative_contract_mw {
  derivative_contract_id  bigint        [pk] // pk_derivative_contract_id (replicated value — not locally generated)
  underlying_type         varchar       [not null] // enum: stocksdb common.underlying_type
  underlying_isin         char(12)
  underlying_index_id     integer
  instrument_type         varchar       [not null] // enum: stocksdb common.derivative_instrument_type
  option_type             varchar // enum: stocksdb common.option_type · NULL for futures
  strike_price            numeric(21,5) // NULL for futures
  expiry_date             date          [not null]
  market_identifier_code  char(4)       [not null]
  tradable_symbol         varchar(64)   [not null]
  lot_size                integer
  tick_size               numeric(21,5)
  contract_data_source_id char(5)       [not null]
  created_on              timestamptz   [not null]

  indexes {
    (market_identifier_code, instrument_type, underlying_type, underlying_isin, underlying_index_id, expiry_date, option_type, strike_price) [unique, name: 'uq_derivative_contract']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Derivative Contract Reference (`_mw`) — StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only option/future contract master. Populated via subscription
  `stocksdb_derivative_reference` from publication `stocksdb_derivative_table`.
  `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` are revoked from `PUBLIC`; incoming foreign keys are
  omitted. Mirrors the source column shape (polymorphic underlying, option-only
  fields nullable). Out of scope for the cash-equity v1 phase but subscribed from
  day one so the polymorphic instrument reference on trading facts resolves once
  F&O is enabled.

  > **Note:** `derivative_contract_id` is a plain `bigint` primary key here (the
  > identity sequence lives on the publisher).

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.strategy_universe_mw`** — `fk_universe_derivative_contract_id` (derivative leg)
  - **`private.signal_tx`** — `fk_signal_derivative_contract_id`
  - **`private.order_tx`** — `fk_order_derivative_contract_id`
  - **`private.position_snapshot_tx`** — `fk_position_derivative_contract_id`
  '''
}


// ============================================================================
// common schema — trading masters (locally owned · read-write)
// ============================================================================

table common.account_mw {
  account_uuid       uuid          [pk, default: `gen_random_uuid()`] // pk_account_uuid
  broker_code        char(5)       [not null, ref: > public.broker_mw.broker_code] // fk_account_broker_code · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_label      varchar(64)   [not null, unique] // uq_account_label
  broker_client_id   varchar(32)   [not null]
  base_currency_code char(3)       [not null, ref: > common.currency_mw.currency_code] // fk_account_base_currency · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  allocated_capital  numeric(21,5) [not null]
  is_active          boolean       [not null, default: true]
  created_on         timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (broker_code, broker_client_id) [unique, name: 'uq_account_broker_client']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Account Master (`mw` = Master-World)

  Normalised registry of trading (DEMAT) accounts. The `account_uuid` surrogate is
  the partition key threaded through **every** transactional fact in `private`,
  isolating multi-account books cleanly from day one (single account today, more
  later — no migration needed). `broker_client_id` is the broker-side identifier
  (not a secret); credentials live in the host secret store.

  `allocated_capital` is the total deployable capital for the account; per-strategy
  slices are governed by `common.strategy_allocation_mw`.

  ### Parents

  - **`public.broker_mw`** — `fk_account_broker_code`
  - **`common.currency_mw`** — `fk_account_base_currency`

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_account_broker_client`: (`broker_code`, `broker_client_id`) — one row per
    client id per broker.

  ### Referenced By

  - Every `private.*_tx` table via `account_uuid`; `common.strategy_allocation_mw`;
    `common.risk_rule_mw`.
  '''
}

table common.strategy_mw {
  strategy_uuid    uuid         [pk, default: `gen_random_uuid()`] // pk_strategy_uuid
  strategy_name    varchar(64)  [not null]
  strategy_version varchar(16)  [not null] // content hash of the parameter set
  strategy_stage   varchar(8)   [not null, default: 'A'] // enum: common.strategy_stage (A, B, C, RETIRED)
  signal_source    varchar(16)  [not null, default: 'STRATEGY'] // enum: common.signal_source
  timeframe        varchar      [not null] // enum: common.timeframe_value
  instrument_kind  varchar(16)  [not null] // enum: private.instrument_kind (EQUITY, DERIVATIVE)
  entry_point      varchar(128) [not null] // python import path, e.g. algotraders.strategies.opening_range
  is_active        boolean      [not null, default: true]
  created_on       timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (strategy_name, strategy_version) [unique, name: 'uq_strategy_name_version']
    (strategy_stage, is_active)       [name: 'ix_strategy_mw_stage_active']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Strategy Master (`mw` = Master-World)

  Definition registry of trading strategies, mirroring the decorator-registry
  pattern used for brokers in `algotraders`. Each row pins a strategy *name* to a
  content-hashed *version* of its parameter set, so every signal, order and backtest
  result traces back to an exact parameterisation.

  - `strategy_stage` drives the automation lifecycle: `A` (signal-only) → `B`
    (human-approved) → `C` (fully automated) → `RETIRED`. Stage promotion is an
    audit-logged action (`STAGE_PROMOTED`).
  - `signal_source` distinguishes native Python strategies (`STRATEGY`) from
    TradingView-webhook (`TRADINGVIEW`) and discretionary (`MANUAL`) sources.
  - `entry_point` is the importable Python path the live/paper/backtest engines load.

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_strategy_name_version`: (`strategy_name`, `strategy_version`).

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.strategy_allocation_mw`** — `fk_allocation_strategy_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_universe_mw`** — `fk_universe_strategy_uuid`
  - **`common.risk_rule_mw`** — `fk_risk_rule_strategy_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`private.signal_tx`** / **`order_tx`** / **`position_snapshot_tx`** / **`pnl_daily_tx`** (nullable)
  '''
}

table common.strategy_allocation_mw {
  allocation_id     integer       [pk, increment] // pk_allocation_id · generated always as identity
  account_uuid      uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_allocation_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid     uuid          [not null, ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_allocation_strategy_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  allocation_policy varchar(24)   [not null] // enum: common.allocation_policy (STATIC_PCT, DYNAMIC_FREEFLOAT)
  allocation_pct    numeric(5, 2) // % of account capital · used when policy = STATIC_PCT
  max_capital       numeric(21,5) // hard ceiling regardless of policy
  is_active         boolean       [not null, default: true]
  created_on        timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, strategy_uuid) [unique, name: 'uq_strategy_allocation']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Strategy Capital Allocation (`mw` = Master-World)

  Normalised junction binding a strategy to an account with its capital mandate.
  Splitting allocation out of `strategy_mw` lets the same strategy definition run on
  multiple accounts with different sizing.

  - `STATIC_PCT` — strategy is capped at `allocation_pct` of the account's
    `allocated_capital`.
  - `DYNAMIC_FREEFLOAT` — strategy draws from unutilised account margin, bounded by
    `max_capital`.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_allocation_account_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_allocation_strategy_uuid`

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_strategy_allocation`: (`account_uuid`, `strategy_uuid`) — one mandate per
    strategy per account.

  ### Check Constraint

  - `ck_allocation_policy_fields` — `STATIC_PCT` requires a positive `allocation_pct`
    in `(0, 100]`; `DYNAMIC_FREEFLOAT` requires `max_capital` to be set.
  '''
}

table common.strategy_universe_mw {
  universe_id            integer [pk, increment] // pk_universe_id · generated always as identity
  strategy_uuid          uuid    [not null, ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_universe_strategy_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16) [not null] // enum: private.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_universe_ses_primary_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint  [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id] // fk_universe_derivative_contract_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  is_active              boolean [not null, default: true]
  created_on             timestamptz [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (strategy_uuid, ses_primary_id, derivative_contract_id) [unique, name: 'uq_strategy_universe'] // composite (NULLS NOT DISTINCT): one instrument per strategy
  }

  note: '''
  ## Strategy Instrument Universe (`mw` = Master-World)

  The set of instruments a strategy is permitted to trade / subscribe to. The live
  engine uses this to drive dynamic tick subscriptions on the ticker service. The
  underlying is polymorphic — exactly one of `ses_primary_id` (equity) or
  `derivative_contract_id` (derivative) is populated, matching `instrument_kind`.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_universe_strategy_uuid`
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** — `fk_universe_ses_primary_id` (nullable)
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** — `fk_universe_derivative_contract_id` (nullable)

  ### Check Constraint

  - `ck_universe_instrument_xor` — exactly one instrument ref set, matching
    `instrument_kind` (`EQUITY` ⇒ `ses_primary_id`; `DERIVATIVE` ⇒
    `derivative_contract_id`).

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_strategy_universe` (`UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT`): (`strategy_uuid`,
    `ses_primary_id`, `derivative_contract_id`).
  '''
}

table common.risk_rule_mw {
  risk_rule_id   integer       [pk, increment] // pk_risk_rule_id · generated always as identity
  risk_scope     varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: common.risk_scope (ACCOUNT, STRATEGY, PORTFOLIO)
  account_uuid   uuid          [ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_risk_rule_account_uuid · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid  uuid          [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_risk_rule_strategy_uuid · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  risk_rule_type varchar(32)   [not null] // enum: common.risk_rule_type
  threshold_value numeric(21,5) [not null]
  threshold_unit varchar(16)   [not null] // PCT · ABS · COUNT
  is_active      boolean       [not null, default: true]
  created_on     timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (risk_scope, is_active) [name: 'ix_risk_rule_mw_scope_active']
    (account_uuid, strategy_uuid, risk_rule_type) [unique, name: 'uq_risk_rule'] // composite (NULLS NOT DISTINCT): one rule of a type per scope target
  }

  note: '''
  ## Risk Rule Master (`mw` = Master-World)

  Config-driven risk limits enforced by the risk manager *before* any order reaches
  the OMS — no code redeploy needed to change a limit. A rule is scoped to an
  account, a strategy, or the whole portfolio (`risk_scope`), and the relevant
  `account_uuid` / `strategy_uuid` is populated accordingly (both null ⇒
  `PORTFOLIO`).

  Covers your stated controls: per-trade stop-loss (`PER_TRADE_SL`), position sizing
  (`POSITION_SIZE`), daily max-loss circuit breaker (`DAILY_MAX_LOSS`), max
  concurrent positions (`MAX_POSITIONS`), single-ISIN exposure cap
  (`SINGLE_ISIN_EXPOSURE`), and sector concentration (`SECTOR_CONC`).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_risk_rule_account_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_risk_rule_strategy_uuid` (nullable)

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_risk_rule` (`UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT`): (`account_uuid`, `strategy_uuid`,
    `risk_rule_type`).

  ### Referenced By

  - **`private.circuit_breaker_tx`** — `fk_circuit_risk_rule_id`
  '''
}


// ============================================================================
// private schema — transactional facts (signals → orders → fills → positions)
// ============================================================================

table private.signal_tx {
  signal_uuid            uuid          [pk, default: `gen_random_uuid()`] // pk_signal_uuid
  account_uuid           uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_signal_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid          uuid          [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_signal_strategy_uuid · nullable (manual / tradingview) · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  signal_source          varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: common.signal_source
  signal_action          varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: private.signal_action
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: private.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer       [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_signal_ses_primary_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint        [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id] // fk_signal_derivative_contract_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  target_price           numeric(21,5)
  stop_loss_price        numeric(21,5)
  suggested_quantity     integer
  signal_status          varchar(24)   [not null, default: 'PENDING'] // enum: private.signal_status
  execution_mode         varchar(12)   [not null] // enum: private.execution_mode
  generated_at           timestamptz   [not null]
  valid_until            timestamptz
  payload                jsonb
  created_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, signal_status) [name: 'ix_signal_tx_account_status']
    (strategy_uuid, generated_at) [name: 'ix_signal_tx_strategy_generated']
    (strategy_uuid, ses_primary_id, derivative_contract_id, generated_at, execution_mode) [unique, name: 'uq_signal'] // composite (NULLS NOT DISTINCT): dedupe identical signals
  }

  note: '''
  ## Signal Transactions (`tx` = Transactional)

  Every trade idea emitted by a strategy, a TradingView webhook, or a manual entry.
  The `signal_uuid` is the **end-to-end trace id**: it threads through `order_tx`,
  `audit_log_tx`, structured logs and Prometheus traces, letting one signal be
  followed across every service.

  Lifecycle: `PENDING` → `VALIDATED` (passed risk) → `APPROVED` (B-stage human gate)
  → routed to OMS; or `REJECTED` / `EXPIRED`. `valid_until` drives auto-expiry of
  stale approvals (60s intraday / 5min swing, configurable per strategy).
  `payload` (jsonb) carries strategy-specific context for audit and replay.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_signal_account_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_signal_strategy_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** — `fk_signal_ses_primary_id` (nullable)
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** — `fk_signal_derivative_contract_id` (nullable)

  ### Check Constraint

  - `ck_signal_instrument_xor` — exactly one instrument ref set, matching `instrument_kind`.

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_signal` (`UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT`): (`strategy_uuid`, `ses_primary_id`,
    `derivative_contract_id`, `generated_at`, `execution_mode`).

  ### Referenced By

  - **`private.order_tx`** — `fk_order_signal_uuid` (nullable — manual orders carry none)
  '''
}

table private.order_tx {
  order_uuid             uuid          [pk, default: `gen_random_uuid()`] // pk_order_uuid (client-side idempotency key)
  signal_uuid            uuid          [ref: > private.signal_tx.signal_uuid] // fk_order_signal_uuid · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_uuid           uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_order_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid          uuid          [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_order_strategy_uuid · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  broker_code            char(5)       [not null, ref: > public.broker_mw.broker_code] // fk_order_broker_code · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: private.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer       [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_order_ses_primary_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint        [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id] // fk_order_derivative_contract_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  order_side             varchar(8)    [not null] // enum: private.order_side
  order_type             varchar(8)    [not null] // enum: private.order_type
  order_variety          varchar(12)   [not null, default: 'REGULAR'] // enum: private.order_variety
  product_type           varchar(12)   [not null] // enum: private.product_type
  quantity               integer       [not null]
  limit_price            numeric(21,5) // NULL for MARKET
  trigger_price          numeric(21,5) // SL / SL_M only
  order_status           varchar(24)   [not null, default: 'PENDING_APPROVAL'] // enum: private.order_status
  broker_order_id        varchar(64) // assigned by broker on submit
  approval_source        varchar(16) // enum: private.approval_source · nullable
  approved_at            timestamptz
  execution_mode         varchar(12)   [not null] // enum: private.execution_mode
  placed_at              timestamptz
  created_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]
  updated_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (broker_code, broker_order_id) [unique, name: 'uq_broker_order_id'] // partial: WHERE broker_order_id IS NOT NULL
    (account_uuid, order_status)   [name: 'ix_order_tx_account_status']
    signal_uuid                    [name: 'ix_order_tx_signal_uuid']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Order Transactions (`tx` = Transactional)

  The order lifecycle, one row per order. `order_uuid` is a **client-generated
  idempotency key** — the OMS persists the order *before* sending to the broker, so
  a crash-restart never double-submits; the broker's `broker_order_id` is linked on
  response. Manual orders carry a `NULL` `signal_uuid`.

  `order_variety` defaults to `REGULAR`; `BRACKET` / `COVER` / `AMO` slot in later
  with no schema change (their extra legs / state are modelled when F&O / advanced
  orders are enabled). For cash-equity v1, `product_type` is typically `CNC`
  (delivery) or `INTRADAY` (MIS).

  ### Parents

  - **`private.signal_tx`** — `fk_order_signal_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_order_account_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_order_strategy_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`public.broker_mw`** — `fk_order_broker_code`
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** — `fk_order_ses_primary_id` (nullable)
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** — `fk_order_derivative_contract_id` (nullable)

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_order_instrument_xor` — exactly one instrument ref set, matching `instrument_kind`.
  - `ck_order_price_fields` — `LIMIT` ⇒ `limit_price` set; `SL` / `SL_M` ⇒
    `trigger_price` set; `MARKET` ⇒ both null.
  - `ck_order_quantity` — `quantity` > 0.

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_broker_order_id` (partial, `WHERE broker_order_id IS NOT NULL`):
    (`broker_code`, `broker_order_id`).

  ### Referenced By

  - **`private.execution_tx`** — `fk_execution_order_uuid`
  '''
}

table private.execution_tx {
  execution_id        bigint        [pk, increment] // pk_execution_id · generated always as identity
  order_uuid          uuid          [not null, ref: > private.order_tx.order_uuid] // fk_execution_order_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_uuid        uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_execution_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  broker_execution_id varchar(64)   [not null]
  filled_quantity     integer       [not null]
  fill_price          numeric(21,5) [not null]
  brokerage           numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  taxes_and_charges   numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  net_amount          numeric(21,5) [not null] // signed cashflow (− on buy, + on sell, net of charges)
  execution_mode      varchar(12)   [not null] // enum: private.execution_mode
  fill_time           timestamptz   [not null]
  created_on          timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (order_uuid, broker_execution_id) [unique, name: 'uq_execution']
    (account_uuid, fill_time)         [name: 'ix_execution_tx_account_fill_time']
    fill_time                         [name: 'ix_execution_tx_fill_time']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Execution (Fill) Transactions (`tx` = Transactional)

  One row per fill — a single order may produce several (partial fills). The
  `(order_uuid, broker_execution_id)` uniqueness makes fill ingestion idempotent
  under broker WebSocket replays. `brokerage` and `taxes_and_charges` are captured at
  fill time for accurate net P&L; the granular charge breakup (STT, exchange txn,
  GST, SEBI, stamp duty) used for ITR reporting lives in the deferred `tax` schema.

  ### Parents

  - **`private.order_tx`** — `fk_execution_order_uuid`
  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_execution_account_uuid`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_execution_quantity` — `filled_quantity` > 0.
  - `ck_execution_price` — `fill_price` ≥ 0; `brokerage` ≥ 0; `taxes_and_charges` ≥ 0.

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_execution`: (`order_uuid`, `broker_execution_id`).
  '''
}

table private.position_snapshot_tx {
  position_snapshot_id   bigint        [pk, increment] // pk_position_snapshot_id · generated always as identity
  account_uuid           uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_position_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid          uuid          [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_position_strategy_uuid · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: private.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer       [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_position_ses_primary_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint        [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id] // fk_position_derivative_contract_id · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  net_quantity           integer       [not null]
  average_price          numeric(21,5) [not null]
  last_traded_price      numeric(21,5)
  realized_pnl           numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  unrealized_pnl         numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  execution_mode         varchar(12)   [not null] // enum: private.execution_mode
  snapshot_time          timestamptz   [not null]
  created_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, strategy_uuid, ses_primary_id, derivative_contract_id, snapshot_time, execution_mode) [unique, name: 'uq_position_snapshot'] // composite (NULLS NOT DISTINCT): one snapshot per book per instant
    (account_uuid, snapshot_time) [name: 'ix_position_snapshot_tx_account_time']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Position Snapshot Transactions (`tx` = Transactional)

  Periodic and event-driven snapshots of the live book, attributed to a strategy
  where known (nullable for account-level / manual positions). Drives the dashboard
  positions view and feeds the risk manager's exposure and concentration checks. The
  underlying is polymorphic — equity (`ses_primary_id`) or derivative
  (`derivative_contract_id`).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_position_account_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_position_strategy_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** — `fk_position_ses_primary_id` (nullable)
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** — `fk_position_derivative_contract_id` (nullable)

  ### Check Constraint

  - `ck_position_instrument_xor` — exactly one instrument ref set, matching `instrument_kind`.

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_position_snapshot` (`UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT`): (`account_uuid`,
    `strategy_uuid`, `ses_primary_id`, `derivative_contract_id`, `snapshot_time`,
    `execution_mode`).
  '''
}

table private.pnl_daily_tx {
  pnl_id          bigint        [pk, increment] // pk_pnl_id · generated always as identity
  pnl_date        date          [not null]
  account_uuid    uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_pnl_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid   uuid          [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_pnl_strategy_uuid · nullable (NULL = account-level aggregate) · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  gross_pnl       numeric(21,5) [not null]
  total_charges   numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  net_pnl         numeric(21,5) [not null]
  realized_pnl    numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  unrealized_pnl  numeric(21,5) [not null, default: 0]
  trade_count     integer       [not null, default: 0]
  execution_mode  varchar(12)   [not null] // enum: private.execution_mode
  created_on      timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (pnl_date, account_uuid, strategy_uuid, execution_mode) [unique, name: 'uq_pnl_daily'] // composite (NULLS NOT DISTINCT): one row per book per day per mode
    (account_uuid, pnl_date) [name: 'ix_pnl_daily_tx_account_date']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Daily P&L Transactions (`tx` = Transactional)

  End-of-day P&L roll-up per account per strategy (a `NULL` `strategy_uuid` row is
  the account-level aggregate). Powers the dashboard P&L charts and the daily-loss
  circuit-breaker baseline. `execution_mode` keeps live, paper and backtest books on
  separate rows so shadow-trading comparisons are a single query.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_pnl_account_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_pnl_strategy_uuid` (nullable)

  ### Composite Unique Constraints

  - `uq_pnl_daily` (`UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT`): (`pnl_date`, `account_uuid`,
    `strategy_uuid`, `execution_mode`).
  '''
}

table private.circuit_breaker_tx {
  circuit_event_id bigint        [pk, increment] // pk_circuit_event_id · generated always as identity
  account_uuid     uuid          [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_circuit_account_uuid · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid    uuid          [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid] // fk_circuit_strategy_uuid · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  risk_rule_id     integer       [not null, ref: > common.risk_rule_mw.risk_rule_id] // fk_circuit_risk_rule_id · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  circuit_scope    varchar(16)   [not null] // enum: common.risk_scope
  threshold_value  numeric(21,5) [not null]
  observed_value   numeric(21,5) [not null]
  tripped_at       timestamptz   [not null]
  reset_at         timestamptz
  is_active        boolean       [not null, default: true]
  created_on       timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, is_active) [name: 'ix_circuit_tx_account_active']
    tripped_at                [name: 'ix_circuit_tx_tripped_at']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Circuit Breaker Transactions (`tx` = Transactional)

  Audit of every circuit-breaker trip — the rule that fired, the threshold, the
  observed value, and when it reset. Trip state is mirrored in Redis for hot reads;
  this table is the durable record. A trip fans out to Telegram and the dashboard.
  Daily-loss breakers reset at the 09:00 IST pre-open; manual override requires the
  kill-switch and an explicit restart flag (logged as `CIRCUIT_OVERRIDE`).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_circuit_account_uuid`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** — `fk_circuit_strategy_uuid` (nullable)
  - **`common.risk_rule_mw`** — `fk_circuit_risk_rule_id`
  '''
}

table private.audit_log_tx {
  audit_id     bigint      [pk, increment] // pk_audit_id · generated always as identity
  account_uuid uuid        [ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid] // fk_audit_account_uuid · nullable (system events) · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  actor_type   varchar(16) [not null] // enum: private.actor_type (SYSTEM, STRATEGY, USER, BROKER)
  actor_id     varchar(64)
  audit_action varchar(48) [not null] // SIGNAL_GENERATED, ORDER_PLACED, ORDER_APPROVED, CIRCUIT_TRIPPED, STAGE_PROMOTED, ...
  entity_type  varchar(32) [not null] // SIGNAL, ORDER, EXECUTION, STRATEGY, RISK_RULE, ACCOUNT
  entity_id    varchar(64) [not null] // uuid / id rendered as text
  signal_uuid  uuid // logical reference · no FK (orphaned / failed entities must still log)
  order_uuid   uuid // logical reference · no FK
  payload      jsonb
  logged_at    timestamptz [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (entity_type, entity_id) [name: 'ix_audit_tx_entity']
    audit_action             [name: 'ix_audit_tx_action']
    logged_at                [name: 'ix_audit_tx_logged_at']
    order_uuid               [name: 'ix_audit_tx_order_uuid']
    signal_uuid              [name: 'ix_audit_tx_signal_uuid']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Audit Log (`tx` = Transactional) — 🔒 **Immutable**

  Append-only record of every consequential action: who (`actor_type` / `actor_id`)
  did what (`audit_action`) to which entity (`entity_type` / `entity_id`), with full
  context in `payload`. The cross-service trace ids (`signal_uuid`, `order_uuid`) are
  stored as **logical references with no FK** — a failed or rejected entity that
  never persisted elsewhere must still be auditable.

  > **Immutability:** `UPDATE` and `DELETE` are revoked from **all** roles; only
  > `INSERT` and `SELECT` are granted. Enforced further by a `BEFORE UPDATE OR
  > DELETE` trigger that raises. This is the regulatory-grade record of which order
  > was placed by which strategy, when, and on whose approval.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** — `fk_audit_account_uuid` (nullable — system-level events carry none)

  ### Accessor & Audit Functions (`dev` schema — no tables)

  | function                              | purpose                                                          |
  |:--------------------------------------|:-----------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `dev.audit_trail_for_order_udf`       | Full ordered event trail for an `order_uuid`.                    |
  | `dev.audit_trail_for_signal_udf`      | Full ordered event trail for a `signal_uuid` (signal → fills).   |
  | `dev.open_positions_udf`              | Latest non-zero position per book from `position_snapshot_tx`.   |
  | `dev.realized_pnl_for_range_udf`      | Realized P&L for an account / strategy over a date range.        |
  | `dev.missing_pnl_dates_udf`           | Audit — trading dates with executions but no `pnl_daily_tx` row. |
  '''
}


// ============================================================================
// logical grouping — drives layout in dbdiagram.io
// ============================================================================

tablegroup bootstrap {
  public.broker_mw
}

tablegroup subscribed_reference {
  common.currency_mw
  common.securities_mw
  common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw
  common.stock_exchange_mw
  common.derivative_contract_mw
}

tablegroup trading_masters {
  common.account_mw
  common.strategy_mw
  common.strategy_allocation_mw
  common.strategy_universe_mw
  common.risk_rule_mw
}

tablegroup trading_facts {
  private.signal_tx
  private.order_tx
  private.execution_tx
  private.position_snapshot_tx
  private.pnl_daily_tx
}

tablegroup risk_and_audit {
  private.circuit_breaker_tx
  private.audit_log_tx
}
